---
import Link from "@/components/Link.astro";
import Layout from "@/layouts/Layout.astro";
import { obfuscate } from "@/utils/security";

const email = "hello@davidhell.com";
const mail = () => obfuscate({ href: `mailto:${email}`, __content: email });
---

<Layout title="Impressum • David Hell" description="Imprint & privacy policy">
  <article class="m-auto w-full max-w-2xl px-4 py-8 sm:px-8">
    <h1 class="mb-6 text-4xl font-bold text-slate-200">Imprint & Privacy</h1>

    <p class="mb-4">
      Protecting your data matters to me. This site only processes what is
      technically needed to run it – no advertising trackers, no user profiles,
      no sharing of your data with third parties for marketing.
    </p>

    <h3 class="mb-2 text-lg font-bold text-slate-200">Contact</h3>

    <p class="mb-8">
      David Hell
      <br />
      Graz, Austria
      <br />
      Email:
      <Link {...obfuscate({ href: `mailto:${email}` })}>
        <span {...obfuscate({ __content: email })}></span>
      </Link>
    </p>

    <h3 class="mb-2 text-lg font-bold text-slate-200">Hosting & delivery</h3>

    <p class="mb-8">
      This site is delivered through <em>Cloudflare Pages</em> (Cloudflare, Inc.,
      USA), served to EU visitors from European edge locations. In doing so, Cloudflare
      processes technical data such as your IP address, browser and the requested
      URL – solely to deliver the content and to protect against attacks, not for
      advertising or profiling. The IP address cannot be anonymised at this level,
      as it is required for delivery. Cloudflare is certified under the EU–US Data
      Privacy Framework. The legal basis is my legitimate interest (Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR).
      <br />
      <Link
        target="_blank"
        rel="external noopener noreferrer nofollow"
        href="https://www.cloudflare.com/privacypolicy/"
      >
        Cloudflare: Privacy Policy
      </Link>
      <br />
      <Link
        target="_blank"
        rel="external noopener noreferrer nofollow"
        href="https://www.cloudflare.com/trust-hub/gdpr/"
      >
        Cloudflare: GDPR compliance
      </Link>
    </p>

    <h3 class="mb-2 text-lg font-bold text-slate-200">Web analytics</h3>

    <p class="mb-8">
      For a rough overview of visitor numbers I use
      <em>Cloudflare Web Analytics</em> – without cookies, without fingerprinting
      and without tracking individual users. The data is only evaluated in aggregate
      and does not allow any conclusions about individual people. Legal basis: legitimate
      interest (Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR).
      <br />
      <Link
        target="_blank"
        rel="external noopener noreferrer nofollow"
        href="https://www.cloudflare.com/web-analytics/"
      >
        Cloudflare Web Analytics: product information
      </Link>
    </p>

    <h3 class="mb-2 text-lg font-bold text-slate-200">Cookies</h3>

    <p class="mb-8">
      This site sets no cookies of its own for tracking, marketing or profiling.
      Cloudflare may set technically necessary cookies as part of security and
      attack protection.
    </p>

    <Link href="/">Back home</Link>
  </article>
</Layout>
